'''Harald Espedal''' (born 4 March 1972) is a Norwegian businessperson.
He is a son of [[Tor Espedal]], and stood out in his early teenages as a stock trade prodigy.<ref name=n988>{{cite news|title=Navn i nyhetene: Tor Espedal|date=31 January 1988|agency=Norwegian News Agency|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He was born in [[Stavanger]], graduated from the [[Norwegian School of Economics]] in 1996 and spent his early career in [[SR-Bank]], [[Vesta (company)|Vesta Forsikring]] and [[Arthur Andersen]]'s Stavanger branch.<ref>{{cite news|title=Harald Espedal blir ny styreleder i Lyse|date=3 March 2015|work=Stavanger Aftenblad|language=Norwegian|page=9}}</ref>
He was the chief executive officer of [[Skagenfondene]] from 2002 to 2014, has chaired the board of [[Lyse Energi]], [[Sandnes Sparebank]] and Espedal & Co, deputy chair of the [[Oslo Stock Exchange]] and [[Stavanger Concert Hall]] and has been a board member of [[Aspelin Ramm]] and the [[Norwegian National Opera and Ballet]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Harald Espedal vurderer forvaltning for andre|date=19 January 2017|work=Rogalands Avis Dagsavisen|language=Norwegian|page=9}}</ref> He has also invested heavily in [[Viking FK]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Skagen-topp inn som Viking-aksjonær|date=15 January 2013|agency=Norwegian News Agency|language=Norwegian}}</ref>
