'''Maurizio Chiarini''' (born 7 September 1950 in [[Ferrara]], [[Italy]]), is an Italian businessman and Chairman of SUFER SpA.

Chiarini graduated from the [[University of Bologna]].with a Political Science degree  with a major in Economics. He began his career as the Director of the Economic and Social Research Centre of Ferrara.

From 1989 to 1995, he was the Chairman of SUFER SpA, a leading company in the Renewable Energy Sector. From 1995 to 1999 he was a partner at SMAER, a management consultancy company in charge of Public Administration, and was a member of the Board of Directors. In 1999, he became the Managing Director of Agea SpA and on April 28, 2005 the [[Board of Directors]] of [[Hera Group]] appointed him [[CEO]], a post he held until 2014.

